1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:04,000
Car Sales Analysis Dashboard

2
00:00:04,000 --> 00:00:08,000
Interactive Power BI Project Overview

3
00:00:09,000 --> 00:00:15,000
This dashboard provides a comprehensive overview
of car sales performance

4
00:00:15,000 --> 00:00:22,000
Key metrics include Total Sales, Total Cars,
Average Price, and Mileage

5
00:00:22,000 --> 00:00:30,000
Users can interact with filters such as
Car Model and Year for dynamic analysis

6
00:00:30,000 --> 00:00:38,000
Sales trends are visualized across multiple years
to identify performance patterns

7
00:00:38,000 --> 00:00:47,000
Fuel type distribution highlights customer preferences
including petrol, diesel, hybrid, and electric vehicles

8
00:00:48,000 --> 00:00:56,000
The Brand and Model Analysis page provides detailed insights
into individual vehicle performance

9
00:00:56,000 --> 00:01:05,000
Users can filter specific car models
to explore their behavior across different years

10
00:01:05,000 --> 00:01:14,000
Transmission analysis compares automatic
and manual vehicle preferences

11
00:01:14,000 --> 00:01:23,000
Fuel type selection allows deeper understanding
of diesel, petrol, hybrid, and electric vehicles

12
00:01:23,000 --> 00:01:32,000
Color trends and customer choices are visualized
to highlight popular selections

13
00:01:32,000 --> 00:01:42,000
Additional insights include accident history,
vehicle features, and model-specific attributes

14
00:01:43,000 --> 00:01:53,000
This showcases key automotive brands
featured in the dataset

15
00:01:53,000 --> 00:02:01,000
It enables comparison of brand performance
across different market segments

16
00:02:01,000 --> 00:02:09,000
These insights help identify strong brands
and their influence on overall sales

17
00:02:10,000 --> 00:02:18,000
The Sales and Market Insights page focuses on
overall business performance

18
00:02:18,000 --> 00:02:26,000
Key indicators include Total Sales,
Total Orders, and Average Price

19
00:02:26,000 --> 00:02:34,000
Sales by condition highlights demand for
new, used, and like-new vehicles

20
00:02:34,000 --> 00:02:45,000
Transmission and color analysis provide insights
into customer buying behavior

21
00:02:46,000 --> 00:02:54,000
This dashboard demonstrates strong skills in
data visualization and analytics

22
00:02:54,000 --> 00:03:02,000
It is designed to transform complex data
into clear and meaningful insights


23
00:03:02,000 --> 00:03:06,000
Built using Power BI, DAX, and a custom JSON theme
for a clean and professional dashboard design

24
00:03:07,000 --> 00:03:16,000
Thank you for watching